caption.text:
New game I've been developing :) more info coming soon.

Upon discovering a powerful magical scroll, the knight was teleported in a portal along with all the lost souls from his world, into a 2D world where they don't belong.  Lost.. Trapped in a world he doesn't belong in. Will our hero free those souls and find his way back to his world?

The underlying meaning behind it is really a journey of self discovery, finding yourself.

I want it to have a somber/sinister feel for the most part, but also with an enlightening tone (as comes with soul searching)

i was looking for a pic on my messenger conversation and i saw this pic shit people can say its just a gun with a cammo but damn it reminded me of a lot of stuff it reminded me of how i used  to come home and play until 2 And then wake up the next day and just take a shower and go to school i was like 14 and this is more than call of duty to me its like my little place were i could go and have a good time even tho it had its rought moments and i encountered really toxic people its super emotional seeing this i was depressed i was trying to get a girl and i failed i still miss her but fuck it i just wish i could go back for just one night and play until 2 Am and have fun with erick and all the crew its just nostalgic af🥺

Phoenix Wright: Ace Attorney (NDS), complete in box

Just picked this up today! Went to a convention about an hour away from home, came back with this as well as a couple other games and a bunch of comics (which I'll be posting tomorrow on @braedenscomix). Although I've never played it on the original hardware, I used to occasionally play an emulated version of this game on PC. For those unaware, the game places you in the role of Phoenix Wright, an attorney who attempts to prove his clients "not guilty". To do this, he must gather information and evidence in investigations, and then present them in trials where he must also cross-examine witnesses and answer questions presented to him by the judge, prosecutor, and occasionally witnesses. Although I only ever played the first two(?) of the game's five trials, I thought it to be a very dynamic game with pretty engaging plotlines, and I really hope to finish it one day. Truly an excellent game.

I finally found my old gaming stash buried under piles of random stuff at my parents house tonight. I’ll post more later this week about the gems that are back in my possession but it’s only fitting on the 23rd birthday of the Nintendo 64 that I finally found my original childhood console. Some games are definitely still missing (Mario Kart 64) but I’m happy to find this after years of searching. I might just have to pick up an Eon Super 64 and get this going on the big screen. BTW I’m as confused as you are as to why I have two versions of GoldenEye and WCW/nWo Revenge (both classics). #n64 #nintendo #nintendo64 #goldeneye #wcw #nwo #wwe #wwf #controller #controllers #memorycard #atomicpurple #instagamer #instagaming #retrocollector #retrocollection #retrocollective #gaming #gameroom #videogame #videogames #videogamer #videogaming #videogamecollector #videogamecollecting #videogamecollection #retrogame #retrogames #retrogaming #retrogamers

Slicing and dicing my way through a graveyard in King’s Quest: Mask of Eternity. caption.text:
In the last area of the game in Super Metroid, Tourian, there is exciting surprise after surprise when you face Mother Brain.

First, it turns into a collosal dinosaur. Then, after you hit it with enough missiles and charged up beam shots, the boss hits Samus with a ridiculously overcharged beam that almost completely  defeats Samus.

When all hope is lost, and you think you were going to see another game over screen, an unlikely hero comes to your rescue!

The same large Metroid (or at least one very similar) that zapped your energy down to 1 just a few rooms beforehand in Tourian, comes to the rescue in a huge way!

That large Metroid takes on Mother Brain, stealing its energy away, and restoring Samus' energy all the way back up. It also heroically shields Samus from a blast from Mother Brain, the damage to which effectively kills the last Metroid (or so we assume). And then another exciting surprise comes in the form of the best weapon by far in the game...the hyper beam!

Which Samus can now use to blast Mother Brain to smithereens!

From Shadowkeep until the new year, this is presumably the last majority update of the year. So, with the major changes from y1 adding in special weapon slots, and y2 new subclasses, this will be the 3rd. So, in my opinion, it's 3 years.

My first twitchcon and it was the best! Got to meet followers, friends and fangirled over some of my fellow streamers😍 A huge thank you to my #1 fan aka my boyfriend for getting a table at omnia and letting my friends dance and enjoy gryffin! I love you so much, thank you for supporting me in everything I do and helping me grow into an outgoing fun person❤️ I’m sorry I got too drunk and forgot to invite some of my other twitch friends, but twitch2020 let’s have everything planned better all go out and drink and club! Sorry for those I did not have a chance to meet, I promise to be more organized next year. I love you all and let’s continue to grow on this awesome platform together❤️❤️❤️ *and pls let’s take pics when I’m not hungover😭*

23 years ago today on September 29th, 1996, Nintendo officially released the Nintendo 64 (N64) console in North America. The successor to Nintendo's NES and SNES consoles was a huge success. Overall, the N64 has sold 32.9 million units worldwide, with its most successful game, Super Mario 64, selling 11.62 million units. Overall, Nintendo released 388 different titles for the N64 between North America, Europe, and Japan. The console was discontinued worldwide on April 30, 2002, leaving behind a legacy that is held very dear to gamers.
